{"url": "https://www.ics.uci.edu/~taylor/classes/221/syllabusWQ08.html", "content": "<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01\rTransitional//EN\">\r<html>\r<head>\r  <meta content=\"text/html; charset=iso-8859-1\"\rhttp-equiv=\"Content-Type\">\r  <meta http-equiv=\"Author\" content=\"Richard N. Taylor\">\r  <meta content=\"Taylor IN4MATX 211\" name=\"KeyWords\"><title>IN4MATX 221 Winter 2008</title>\r\r  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\">\r  <style type=\"text/css\">\r<!--\r.style1 {color: #666666}\r.style2 {color: #000000}\r-->\r  </style>\r</head>\r\r\r<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><font face=\"Verdana\">\r\rInformatics 221: Software Architecture </font></h2>\r<div style=\"text-align: center;\">\r  <p><font face=\"Verdana\"><b>\r  Winter Quarter 2008</b></font></p>\r  <p><strong><font face=\"Verdana\">Course Code 37220 </font></strong></p>\r  <p><i>Last update:\r      <!-- #BeginDate format:Am1 -->February 7, 2008<!-- #EndDate -->\r  </i></p>\r</div>\r\r&nbsp;<br>\r\r\r<table width=\"60%\" cellspacing=\"8\">\r<tbody>\r<tr>\r<td align=\"right\">\r\t<p>\r\r\t<b>Instructor:</b></p>\r\r</td>\r<td>\r\t<p>\r\t<a href=\"http://www.ics.uci.edu/%7Etaylor/\">Richard N. Taylor </a>\r\t</p>\r\r</td>\r</tr>\r\r<tr>\r\r<td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\">\r\t<p>\r\t<b>Email:</b></p>\r\r</td>\r<td>\r\t<p>\r\t(taylor [at] ics [dot] uci [dot] edu)<br>\r\tTo ensure a response to your email, please include\r\"Informatics 221\" in the\r\tsubject line and send your email from a UCI\raccount.\r\t</p>\r\r</td>\r</tr>\r<tr>\r<td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\">\r\t<p>\r\r\t<b>Office hours:</b>\r\t</p>\r</td>\r<td> After class, or by email appointment<br>\r\r</td>\r\r</tr>\r<tr>\r<td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\">\r\t<p>\r\t<b>Lectures: </b></font>\r\t</p>\r</td>\r<td>\r\t<p>\r\r\tTuesday and Thursday 2:00 - 3:20 p.m.<strong>,</strong> DBH 1423 </p>\r\r</td>\r</tr>\r<tr>\r<td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\">\r\t<b>Web site:</b>\r</td>\r<td>\r\t<a\rhref=\"http://www.ics.uci.edu/%7Etaylor/classes/221/syllabusWQ08.html\">http://www.ics.uci.edu/~taylor/classes/221/syllabusWQ08.html</a>\r</td>\r\r</tr>\r\r<!--\r<tr>\r<td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\">\r\t<b>EEE Noteboard:</b>\r\r</td>\r<td>\r\t<a\rhref=\"http://eee.uci.edu/toolbox/noteboard/index.php?board=2607\">http://eee.uci.edu/toolbox/noteboard/index.php?board=2607</a><br>\r\t</p>\r</td>\r</tr>\r-->\r\r</tbody>\r</table>\r\r\r<h3>What's New? </h3>\r<ul>\r  <li></li>\r  <li>[January 8, 2008] Website goes live on EEE. </li>\r</ul>\r<p><font face=\"Verdana\"><font size=\"-1\"><a\rhref=\"#description\">Description</a>\r  - <font face=\"Verdana\"><a href=\"#readings\">Textbook and Readings</a> - </font><a href=\"#schedule\">Schedule</a> - <a\rhref=\"#grading\">Grading</a> - <a\rhref=\"#policies\">Policies</a>\r  \r  </font>\r</font></p>\r<hr width=\"100%\">\r\r<h3>\r<a name=\"description\"></a><b>Description</b></font></h3>\r<p><b><a\rhref=\"http://www.editor.uci.edu/07-08/ics/ics.7.htm\">Catalog\rdescription:</a></b></p>\r\r<p>Study of the concepts, representation techniques, development methods, and\r  tools for architecture-centric software engineering. Topics include domain-specific\r  software architectures, architectural styles, architecture description languages,\rsoftware connectors, and dynamism in architectures. Formerly ICS 223.</p>\r<p>\r<hr width=\"100%\">\r<a name=\"readings\" id=\"readings\"></a>\r<h3>Textbook (REQUIRED)</h3>\r<p><strong>Software Architecture: Foundations, Theory, and Practice.</strong> Richard\r  N. Taylor, Nenad Medvidovic, and Eric M. Dashofy. Copyright &copy; 2009 John\r  Wiley &amp; Sons, Inc. (ISBN: 9780470167748)</p>\r<p>A preprint of this textbook will be  available for purchase in class; details\r  in class. </p>\r<hr width=\"100%\">\r\r<h3><font face=\"Verdana\"><a\rname=\"schedule\"></a>Schedule</font></h3>\r\r<p>\rThe schedule is subject to change.&nbsp;\r<table width=100% height=\"968\" border=1 cellpadding=\"3\">\r\r  <tr>\r  \t<th width=\"7%\">Week</th>\r  \t<th colspan=\"2\">Date</th>\r  \t<th width=\"34%\">Topic</th>\r  \t<th width=\"34%\">Individual Lecture Topics</th>\r\r  \t<th width=\"14%\">Slide design and/or presentation</th>\r  \t<th width=\"13%\" bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\"><span class=\"style2\">Readings</span></th>\r\r  \t<th width=\"18%\" bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\">Homework</th>\r  </tr>\r<tr>\r  <td rowspan=\"2\" class=\"week\"> 1    <td width=\"7%\" rowspan=\"8\" class=\"date\">  <p align=\"center\">J</p>\r    <p align=\"center\">A</p>\r    <p align=\"center\">N</p>\r    <p align=\"center\">U</p>\r    <p align=\"center\">A</p>\r    <p align=\"center\">R</p>\r    <p align=\"center\">Y</p>\r    <td width=\"7%\" class=\"date\">8 Tu \r    <td rowspan=\"2\">Introduction    </td>\r    <td>The Big Idea </td>\r  <td class=\"ok\">Taylor</td>\r      <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\">Chapter 1       \r      <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\">&nbsp;</td>\r\r  </tr>\r  <tr>\r    <td class=\"date\">10&nbsp;Th\r    <td>Architectures in Context     \r    <td class=\"ok\">Taylor</td>\r    <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\">Chapter 2     \r    <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\" class=\"due\">&nbsp;</td>\r  </tr>\r  <tr>\r    <td rowspan=\"2\" class=\"week\"> 2    <!-- - - - - - - -3- - - - - - - -->\r    <td class=\"date\">15&nbsp;Tu\r    <td rowspan=\"2\">Basic Concepts and Introduction to Design     </td>\r    <td>Basic Concepts </td>\r\r      <td>(Medvidovic)</td>\r      <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\">Chapter 3 </td>\r      <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\">&nbsp;</td>\r  </tr>\r  <tr>\r    <td class=\"date\">17&nbsp;Th\r    <td>Designing Architectures     \r    <td class=\"ok\">Taylor    \r    <td rowspan=\"3\" bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\">Chapter 4 </td>\r      <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\" class=\"due\">&nbsp;</td>\r  </tr>\r  <tr>\r    <td rowspan=\"2\" class=\"week\"> 3    <!-- - - - - - - -4- - - - - - - -->\r    <td class=\"date\">22&nbsp;Tu<!-- <td>Aspect Oriented Programming</td>\r      <td>Lopes</td>\r      <td><a href=\"http://www.ics.uci.edu/%7Etaylor/ICS221/papers/AOP.pdf\">[KLM+97]</a>\r\t      <br>and optionally\r\t      <br><a href=\"http://www.ics.uci.edu/%7Eredmiles/ics221-FQ03/papers/TDBL00.pdf\">[TDBL00]</a> </td>\r-->\r    <td rowspan=\"2\">Designing Architectures </td>\r    <td>Architectural Styles </td>\r\t<td>Taylor</td>\r\t<td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\">Homework #1 due</td>\r  </tr>\r\r  <tr>\r    <td class=\"date\">24&nbsp;Th</td>\r      <td>Styles and Greenfield Design</td>\r    <td>Taylor*</td>\r    <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\" class=\"due\">&nbsp;</td>\r  </tr>\r\r  <tr>\r    <td rowspan=\"2\" class=\"week\"> 4    <!-- - - - - - - -5- - - - - - - -->\r    <td class=\"date\">29&nbsp;Tu</td>\r      <td rowspan=\"2\">Connectors</td>\r      <td>Software Connectors</td>\r      <td class=\"ok\">(Medvidovic)*</td>\r      <td rowspan=\"2\" bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\">Chapter 5 </td>\r      <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\">&nbsp;</td>\r  </tr>\r\r  <tr>\r    <td class=\"date\">31&nbsp;Th\r    <td>Choosing Connectors </td>\r      <td>(Medvidovic)</td>\r    <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\" class=\"due\">&nbsp;</td>\r  </tr>\r\r  <tr>\r    <td rowspan=\"2\" class=\"week\"> 5    <br>      <!-- - - - - - - -6- - - - - - - -->\r    <td width=\"7%\" rowspan=\"8\" class=\"date\">        <p align=\"center\">F</p>\r    <p align=\"center\">E</p>\r    <p align=\"center\">B</p>\r    <p align=\"center\">R</p>\r    <p align=\"center\">U</p>\r    <p align=\"center\">A</p>\r    <p align=\"center\">R</p>\r    <p align=\"center\">Y</p>\r    <td class=\"date\">5&nbsp;Tu\r    <td rowspan=\"2\">Modeling</td>\r    <td>Introduction to Modeling </td>\r      <td class=\"ok\">(Dashofy)</td>\r      <td rowspan=\"2\" bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\">Chapter 6 </td>\r      <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\">&nbsp;</td>\r</tr>\r\r  <tr>\r    <td class=\"date\">7&nbsp;Th\r    <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\">Modeling and Notations</td>\r    <td>(Dashofy)</td>\r    <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\" class=\"due\">&nbsp;</td>\r\r  </tr>\r\r  <tr>\r    <td rowspan=\"2\" class=\"week\"> 6    <!-- - - - - - - -7- - - - - - - -->\r    <td class=\"date\">12&nbsp;Tu\r    <td rowspan=\"2\">Visualization</td>\r    <td>Visualizing Software Architectures </td>\r    <td>(Dashofy)</td>\r    <td rowspan=\"2\" bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\">Chapter 7 </td>\r      <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\">&nbsp;</td>\r  </tr>\r\r\r  <tr>\r    <td class=\"date\">14&nbsp;Th\r    <td>Visualization, continued </td>\r    <td>(Dashofy)</td>\r      <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\" class=\"due\">&nbsp;</td>\r  </tr>\r\r  <tr>\r    <td rowspan=\"2\" class=\"week\"> 7    <!-- - - - - - - -8- - - - - - - -->\r    <td height=\"46\" class=\"date\">19&nbsp;Tu</td>\r      <td>Analysis</td>\r      <td>Analysis of Software Architectures </td>\r    <td>(Medvidovic)*</td>\r      <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\">Chapter 8 (selections) </td>\r      <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\">Homework #2 due</td>\r      <!--\r      <td><a\rhref=\"http://www.ics.uci.edu/~taylor/ICS221/slides/ICS221CSCWDourish.ppt\">Computer-supported cooperative work</a>\r      <td class=\"ok\">Dourish\r      <td><a\rhref=\"http://www.ics.uci.edu/~redmiles/ics221-FQ03/papers/AO00.pdf\">[AO00]</a>\r      <br><a\rhref=\"http://www.ics.uci.edu/~redmiles/ics221-FQ03/papers/Gru94.pdf\">[Gru94]</a>\r      -->\r  </tr>\r\r  <tr>\r    <td height=\"46\" class=\"date\">21&nbsp;Th\r    <td rowspan=\"2\">Implementation    </td>\r    <td>Implementing Architectures</td>\r\t<td>(Dashofy)*</td>\r\t<td rowspan=\"2\" bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\">Chapter 9 </td>\r\t<td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\" class=\"due\">&nbsp;</td>\r  </tr>\r\r  <tr>\r    <td rowspan=\"2\" class=\"week\"> 8    <!-- - - - - - - -9- - - - - - - -->\r    <td class=\"date\">26&nbsp;Tu\r    <td>Implementation Techniques \r    <td>(Dashofy)*</td>\r    <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\">&nbsp;</td>\r  </tr>\r\r\r  <tr>\r    <td class=\"date\"> 28 &nbsp;Th\r    <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\">Non-functional Properties</td>\r    <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\">Designing for NFPs </td>\r      <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\">(Medvidovic)*</td>\r      <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\">Chapter 12 (selections)</td>\r      <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\" class=\"due\">&nbsp;</td>\r  </tr>\r\r  <tr>\r    <td rowspan=\"2\" class=\"week\"> 9    <!-- - - - - - - 10- - - - - - -->\r    <td width=\"7%\" rowspan=\"5\" align=\"center\" class=\"date\">     <p>M</p>\r      <p>A</p>\r      <p>R</p>\r      <p>C</p>\r      <p>H    </p>\r    <td class=\"date\"> 4 &nbsp;Tu</td>\r\r      <td>Architectures in the Real-World </td>\r      <td>Applied Architectures </td>\r      <td>Taylor</td>\r      <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\">Chapter 11 </td>\r\t  <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\">&nbsp;</td>\r  </tr>\r\r\r  <tr>\r    <td class=\"date\">6&nbsp;Th</td>\r      <td rowspan=\"2\">Domain-Specific Software Engineering </td>\r      <td>Introduction to DSSE </td>\r      <td>(D/M)</td>\r      <td rowspan=\"2\" bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\">Chapter 15 </td>\r      <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\" class=\"due\">&nbsp;</td>\r  </tr>\r\r\r  <tr>\r    <td rowspan=\"2\" class=\"week\">10      \r    <td class=\"date\">11&nbsp;Tu</td>\r      <td>DSSE and Product Lines </td>\r      <td>(D/M)</td>\r      <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\" class=\"due\">&nbsp;</td>\r\r  </tr>\r\r\r  <tr>\r    <td class=\"date\">13 Th </td>\r    <td>Standards</td>\r    <td>Standards</td>\r    <td>(Dashofy)</td>\r    <td>Chapter 16 (selected) </td>\r    <td>&nbsp;</td>\r  </tr>\r  <tr><td class=\"week\" rowspan=\"1\">Exam <!-- - - - - - -Exam - - - - - -->\r    <td class=\"date\">20 Th </td>\r      <td>&nbsp;</td>\r      <td>Exam\r          from 1:30 - 3:30 </td>\r      <td>&nbsp;</td>\r      <td><span class=\"style1\"></span></td>\r      <td>&nbsp;</td>\r  </tr>\r\r</table>\r\r<hr width=\"100%\">\r\r<h3><font face=\"Verdana\"><a name=\"grading\"></a>Grading and\rEvaluations</font></h3>\r\r<p><b>Grading.</b><br>\rThere are 3 elements to your grade: a final exam, homework,  and class\r  attendance and participation. More details TBA.\r<p>\r<p><strong>Summary of Assessment: </strong> </p>\r<table summary=\"Grading\">\r  <tr>\r    <td>Homework</td>\r    <td>70%<br>\r  </tr>\r  <tr>\r    <td>Final exam </td>\r    <td>20%<br>\r  </tr>\r  <tr>\r    <td>Class attendance and participation</td>\r    <td>10%</td>\r  </tr>\r  <!--\r  <tr>\r  \t<td>Final exam</td>\r  \t<td>20%</td>\r  </tr>\r-->\r</table>\r<p> No grades of incomplete (I) will be given for this course.&nbsp;</p>\r<hr width=\"100%\">\r\r\r<h3><font face=\"Verdana\"><a\rname=\"policies\"></a>Policies</font></h3>\r\r<p><b>Course Evalutions. </b>The online evaluation window for winter quarter\r  will run from TBA through TBA.  </p>\r<p><b>Cheating. </b>The <a\rhref=\"http://www.senate.uci.edu/senateweb/printed.asp?active_page_id=754\">UCI\r  academic honesty policy</a> applies. Consequences of\r  cheating in this class:\r  a letter in your UCI file, and the course grade is lowered,\r  most likely to\r  F. Material that is copied from books or Web pages needs to\r  be quoted and\r  the source <em>must</em> be given.  If you plagarize, you run the severe risk\r  of failing the class, in a most disgraceful manner. </p>\r<p><b>Disabilities. </b> If you need an accommodation\rbecause of a disability, please contact\rthe instructor and the <a\rhref=\"http://www.disability.uci.edu/\">Disability Services\rCenter</a> as soon as possible.\r\r<hr width=\"100%\">\r\r<font face=\"Verdana\"><font size=\"-1\"><br>\r<i><font\rsize=\"-1\">(C) University of California, 2008.\r</font></i></font>\r</font>\r</body></html>\r\r\r<!--\r<td><a\rhref=\"other/ics221.formalSpecification.2004.ppt\">Formal\rspecification methods</a></td>\r      <td class=\"ok\">Alspaugh\r      <td><a\rhref=\"http://www.ics.uci.edu/%7Etaylor/ICS221/papers/e1089.pdf\">[vLW98]</a>\r\r      <br><a\rhref=\"http://www.ics.uci.edu/%7Etaylor/ICS221/papers/HLK95.pdf\">[HLK95]</a>\r\r\r      <td class=\"ok\">Scenario analysis\r      <td><span class=\"ok\">Alspaugh</span>\r      <td><a\rhref=\"http://springerlink.metapress.com/link.asp?id=v90uxu73cw29drka\">[AP98]</a>\r      <br><a\rhref=\"http://doi.acm.org/10.1145/225434.225462\">[Pot95]</a>\r\r\r\r-->\r", "encoding": "ascii"}